<font color="#FF0000">SCREAMS</font><br>
<tt>Fri Aug  1  0:59:30 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
When I go into a resturant or department store... anywhere and I hear children crying... I am devastated.  I am carried away to a horrible place in time.  It is a stimuli that I recognize but cannot conquer.<br>
I am not so much plagued by the sounds of men screaming, but on occassions I am awakened by my own screaming.  Sometimes, I don't know what for.<br>
Conscienciously, I can recall the sounds of wounded begging for God to save them or telling their mothers that they love them.  Bad trip!<br><br>
Mustang Two Four
